From: filamind <abdelmonemawad@hotmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] iot_drivers: make save_conf_server arguments optional

Allow save_conf_server() to be called with only a URL, omitting the token,
db_uuid and enterprise_code. This is required so the new "set server URL"
endpoint can store a bare URL without forcing the caller to supply the
auxiliary fields (which the user does not have at that point).

The existing pairing flow still passes all four values, so behavior is
unchanged for the standard flow.

---
 addons/iot_drivers/tools/helpers.py | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/addons/iot_drivers/tools/helpers.py b/addons/iot_drivers/tools/helpers.py
--- a/addons/iot_drivers/tools/helpers.py
+++ b/addons/iot_drivers/tools/helpers.py
@@ -99,7 +99,7 @@ def require_db(function):
     return wrapper


-def save_conf_server(url, token, db_uuid, enterprise_code, db_name=None):
+def save_conf_server(url, token='', db_uuid='', enterprise_code='', db_name=None):
     """
     Save server configurations in odoo.conf
     :param url: The URL of the server
